race.comment: Looks to be two chances. CHARM STONE (5) is hard to ignore having won the G1 Manikato Stakes first up, doing it impressively as well. She had the perfect run there and did start $31 in a fairly thin G1 sprint, but she's now a dual G1 winner in at set weights here. TROPICUS (3) has come back very well. He was dominant first up and then awfully brave in the G2 Schillaci last time, unable to cross, taken on in front as the other leaders were beaten out of sight. Only Giga Kick with the perfect swooping run got past him late, and with a kinder run on pace he'll be very hard to catch. NIANCE (7) was behind TROPICUS last time and had her chance to get past him late but still ran well and is in the mix. BRIDAL WALTZ (8) was good fresh behind War Machine albeit he dropped the field. Fitter now and is some hope. VESTAS (9) charged home late fresh but this is harder and she'll give them a start again.
